articles.author: Matthew Loh
articles.title: Russia Just Lost One of Its Weirdest Wartime Income Streams - Business Insider
articles.description: Even while at war, Ukraine piped Russian gas to Europe. Moscow earned an estimated $5 billion in 2024, while Ukraine raked in up to $1 billion in fees.
articles.content:
Russia is no longer able to send natural gas to Europe through Ukraine's pipelines after a five-year deal, struck before the war began, expired on Wednesday.
